Ingredients

* 1/2 cup brown sugar
* 1/3 cup soy sauce
* 2 tablespoons hoisin sauce
* 2 tablespoons peeled and ginger
* dried red pepper flakes
* 1/2 teaspoon chopped garlic
* 1 tablespoon fresh lime juice
* 1 1/2 - 2 lbs salmon fillets

Steps

1. Cook on medium heat sugar, soy sauce, ginger, dash of red pepper flakes, garlic, and lime juice for 15 - 20 minutes or until the sauce forms a glaze
1. Preheat broiler
1. Place salmon on a covered in foil broiler pan and baste with sauce
1. Let sit for 15 minutes
1. Broil until cooked through - 6 - 8 minutes
1. Remove from heat and baste again before serving
